<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}-{8}{y}=-{43}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{2}{x}-{6}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},{1}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+-{8}{y}=-{43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}=-{43}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{43}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}}}{{5}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{\left(\frac{{-{43}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}}}{{5}}\right)}+-{6}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{2}}{{5}}\cdot{\left(-{43}\right)}--\frac{{2}}{{5}}{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{17.2}-{\left(-{3.2}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3.2}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}={8}-{17.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3.2}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}=-{9.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3.2}+{\left(-{6}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{9.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9.2}{y}=-{9.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{9.2}}{{-{{9.2}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={1}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+-{8}{\left({1}\right)}=-{43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+{\left(-{8}\right)}=-{43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}=-{43}-{\left(-{8}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}=-{35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{35}}{{5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},{1}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

